#### Rotary Training

[No. 1 Flying Training School](/No._1_Flying_Training_School_RAF) (No. 1 FTS), formerly known as the [Defence Helicopter Flying School](/Defence_Helicopter_Flying_School), is based at [RAF Shawbury](/RAF_Shawbury) in Shropshire. This institution provides fundamental helicopter pilot training for all [UK armed forces](/British_Armed_Forces). It operates a fleet of twenty-nine [Airbus Juno HT1](/Eurocopter_EC135) helicopters. No. 1 FTS is composed of two primary elements: 2 Maritime Air Wing (2 MAW) and No. 9 Regiment. 2 MAW encompasses [No. 660 Squadron](/No._660_Squadron_AAC) of the [Army Air Corps](/Army_Air_Corps_(United_Kingdom)) (AAC) and [705 Naval Air Squadron](/705_Naval_Air_Squadron), both of which deliver basic helicopter flying training. No. 9 Regiment, in turn, comprises [No. 60 Squadron](/No._60_Squadron_RAF) of the RAF and [No. 670 Squadron](/No._670_Squadron_RAF) of the AAC, specializing in advanced helicopter flying training. Additionally, [No. 202 Squadron](/No._202_Squadron_RAF) is also an integral part of No. 1 FTS, operating the [Airbus Jupiter HT1](/Eurocopter_EC145) at [RAF Valley](/RAF_Valley). A comprehensive system, ensuring a steady supply of skilled helicopter pilots.

